With mapstruct `1.5.0` (currently at `1.5.0.Beta2`) the `@Condition` annotation is introduced. With this you can define your own checks for when to map values.

for example to map all `int`s that are not `0` you could do the following:
```
@Condition
boolean shouldMap(int number) {
    return number != 0;
}
```

[For more information see Conditional Mapping at the mapstruct reference guide.][1]


  [1]: https://mapstruct.org/documentation/dev/reference/html/#conditional-mapping

